climbs.name: The Call of the Wild
climbs.fa: Tom Slater and Paul Bernard, May 4, 2005

content.description: Climb to crux pulling over a bulge protected by second bolt and continue to easier ground above.
content.protection: 7 bolts to anchor with quicklinks, which can be accessed by walking around top to right.
content.location: Located on the shorter, far right side of the Swiss Cheese Wall. Look for bolted line to the right of cave.

content.description: A long face climb up "clean" rock.  Still enough pebbles and debris pulling/falling to keep it exciting!
content.location: Starts just left of the large oak tree in the front of the main formation.

content.description: Front of main formation, starting on long ledge 20 feet left of Wild.  Dynamic moves over crux bulges, then follow thin water streak to anchor chains.  Rap 100 feet or traverse to Wild.
content.location: Locate Wild, move two climbs left.

content.description: Climb face on mostly solid rock for two pitches to gain the sloping topout of the Swiss Cheese Wall.
content.location: Begin the route on a boulder sitting adjacent to the wall. Pull the moves from the ground to the right for a 5.10a variation.

content.description:
This route is a total blast! Start just left of the bolts at the start, then just go up them. Cool holes and cobbles get you up to a difficult finish. TR it if you're panicky. On Outerspace wall, behind Big Rocks.

If you are not scared of less than perfect rock, there is a whole new world for you to explore out here!
Cobble pinching over cruxy bulges. Located on Outerspace wall, behind Big Rocks proper. TR it if you're insecure on this rock.
To quote from the Slater guide, "Starts near the dead tree. Follow a trough up to an overhang. From big jugs, dyno up and left then ascend cobbles to the top."
content.location: Outer Space Wall, which is the 70 foot cliff on the backside of the Big Rocks formation. It gets afternoon shade.
